FILE: (Stan Honda, AFP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories San Jose - Wild pigs are eating front yards in at least one Northern California neighbourhood.KNTV reports that the pigs strike in the middle of the night, digging up front lawns in the Evergreen neighbourhood in South San Jose.Resident Rod Murchison says there are about 20 wild boars that have destroyed more than half a dozen lawns in the neighbourhood over the past week.Some pigs have also eaten geranium plants.Residents say they believe the pigs are coming from nearby ranch land.One resident put up a device that shines a red light, simulating a pig predator, hoping it will be enough to keep the hungry grub hunters away.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.